** OVERALL RESPONSIBILITIES
HR Supervisor Role is focused on understanding what people need and knowing how to provide it. If you’re a people-person looking to start a career in the exciting world of HR, this is the best place to dive in. We’re in search of a qualified and resourceful HR Supervisor to support our HR department in ensuring smooth and efficient business operations. The HR Supervisor will have both administrative and strategic responsibilities, helping us to plan and administer important functions, such as staffing, training and development, and compensation and benefits. We understand that our business thrives when our personnel thrive, and that starts by hiring the right HR professionals.

** Objective:
- Assist in developing and executing personnel procedures and policies, providing guidance and interpretation for business operations
- Participate in development of HR objectives and systems, including metrics, queries, and standard reports for ongoing company requirements
- Assist in administering benefits, compensation, and employee performance programs
- Suggest new procedures and policies to continually improve efficiency of the HR department and organization as a whole, and to improve employee experience
- Ensure legal compliance of HR state and federal regulations and applicable employment laws, and update policies and/or procedures as required

1.1 Recruitment
- Prepare paperwork, schedule, and facilitate smooth new hire onboarding process, coordinating with cross-functional departments to deliver an exceptional first-day experience;
- Handle all administrative tasks for onboarding, new hire orientation, and exit interviews, including entering data into HR information systems and auditing for accuracy and
compliance;
- Manage all recruitment process and report to the HR Manager for the recruitment planning;
- Perform all jobs posting as well as engaging with recruitment agents to make sure to recruit the best candidates;
- Track and follow up probation and inform supervisor for evaluation in a timely manner;
- Process employment contract and make sure the contracts are ready for the employee to sign by ensuring the approval from the management;
- Conduct staff orientation regarding to company’s policies and procedures, benefits relating to the position, and other necessary information to make sure new staff are well understood;
- Facilitate with ministry officer relating to all relevant HR compliances and auditing;
- Track staff movement (in and out) and update to the ministry as required by law;
- Assist HR manager in clearing payout compensation for employee when the contract is terminated;
- Conduct exit interview with employee and update the report to the HR/Admin manager;

1.2 Administration
- Provide an effective and dedicated HR advisory service to employees in relation to absence and health issues, conduct and capability, grievance matters, organizational change, and all other employee-relations matters
- Assist in the communication, interpretation, and upkeep of employee handbook, employee directory, and organizational chart, and contributes to the development of policies

1.3 Compensation & Benefit
- Be the primary backup for payroll processing, including; bi-weekly and semi-monthly updates to employee files, bonus/incentive pay, tracking vacation/sick pay, importing
expense reimbursements, inputting exceptions, hourly employee validations, and benefit changes
- Handle all payments to NSSF as required by law
- Inform staff movement and processing the payroll

4. REPORTING/COLLABORATIONS
